+   * The relative URL from the HTTP method annotation (e.g., {@link retrofit2.http.GET @GET}),
+   * before path parameter substitution.
+   *
+   * <p>This is equivalent to {@link #annotationUrl()} and is provided for clarity when used in
+   * interceptors that need to identify the request target.
+   *
+   * <p>This value will be null if one of the method's parameters is annotated
+   * {@link retrofit2.http.Url @Url}, or if this Invocation was created without a URL.
+   */
+  @Nullable
+  public String relativeUrl() {
+    return annotationUrl;
+  }
